üìä Introduction

This project is an interactive sales analytics dashboard built using Power BI. It provides a comprehensive analysis of a coffee shop's sales data, enabling users to explore key performance metrics and gain valuable insights into customer behavior, product trends, and regional performance. The dashboard is designed to support strategic decision-making through data-driven insights.

üìç Dashboard Objectives  

The main goals of this dashboard are to:  

- Monitor sales performance over time  
- Identify top-selling products and customer preferences  
- Analyze regional sales trends  
- Understand average purchase behavior  
- Provide an interactive and user-friendly interface for exploring data  

Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)  
The dashboard highlights the following KPIs:

- Total Customers: Tracks the number of unique customers to evaluate customer base growth.  
- Total Revenue: Displays the total income generated from all sales.  
- Average Sales: Calculates the average amount spent per transaction.  
- Quantity Sold: Sums the total number of units sold.  
- Total Sales: A combined view reflecting both volume and revenue of sales activity.  

These KPIs provide a high-level view of business performance and help identify trends and areas for improvement.

Interactive Filters and Slicers
Users can explore the data using the following slicers:

Coffee Type: Filter data based on different types of coffee sold.

Roast Type: Drill into the performance of light, medium, or dark roasts.

Size: Analyze sales data by product size (e.g., small, medium, large).

Country: View and compare sales performance across different countries or regions.

These filters allow for dynamic, flexible exploration of the dataset, enabling users to gain insights based on specific criteria.

Tools and Technologies
Power BI: Data visualization and dashboard development

DAX: Used for creating custom calculations and measures

Excel/CSV: For raw data input (if applicable)

Features
Clean and intuitive user interface

Interactive visualizations with real-time filtering

Multiple charts and graphs for visual comparison

Drill-down functionality for deeper insights

Usage
To view and interact with the dashboard:

Download the .pbix file from this repository.

Open it using Power BI Desktop.

Use the slicers and filters to explore the data based on your interests.

Potential Use Cases
Business performance reviews

Marketing and product strategy planning

Sales forecasting and resource allocation

Market segmentation and targeting
